article.headline: Valparaiso 83, Concordia University (WI) 57
article.story: VALPARAISO, Ind. -- Brandon Wood scored 21 points and Cory Johnson 20 as Valparaiso defeated Concordia, Wis., 83-57 Saturday night. Ryan Broekhoff scored 17 points in 17 minutes for Valparaiso (5-6) and Michael Rogers had 11. The Crusaders, who led 51-22 at halftime and by 32 points early in the second half, outrebounded Concordia 45-32, and shot 53 percent from the field while limiting the visitors to 31 percent shooting. Valparaiso also enjoyed a 48-12 advantage in points in the paint. Mitchell Schneider, with 17 points, was the only Concordia player in double figures. The Falcons (5-6) are members of NCAA Division III.
